    "description": "kin-15 Watt straight-line linkage \u2014 James Watt's 1784 4-bar parallel motion. Planar 4-bar (chassis + crank_left + coupler + crank_right) producing an APPROXIMATE vertical straight line at the coupler midpoint M. Operator-noted regression value: 'the straight line is an approximation, not exact \u2014 visual diff should show the slight curve at the extremes.' Same topology family as kin_11 (single closed loop) but with the Watt-specific 60\u00b0/120\u00b0 crank angles + 40 mm short coupler. Forward-dynamics integrates 2s under 250 N\u00b7mm constant left-crank torque; Canary's per-frame scrub (Session B+) steps AnimSlider through 11 values to animate the GIF. Phase 4.6.F.6 \u2014 fills the original prompt's deferred kin_15 slot.",
