        "vlmDescription": "James Watt's 1784 straight-line 4-bar linkage shown as a bound mechanism at a single time-step of a 2-second forward-dynamics integration. Three bound bodies are rendered as thin pipes: a slightly-thicker A\u2013M\u2013B coupler triangle (M is the trace midpoint) and two thinner rocker arms \u2014 O\u2192A (left crank, pivoting from world origin) and P\u2192B (right crank, pivoting from (100,0)). At slider=0 the design pose has both cranks pointing inward and upward at 60\u00b0/120\u00b0 from world +X. As the slider advances, a constant 250 N\u00b7mm torque on the left crank rotates the linkage; the coupler midpoint M traces an APPROXIMATE vertical straight line. A faint design-pose skeleton (frame triads at O and P, joint circles at A, B, M) is overlaid via Preview Diagram in Display Mode 2."
